# Old Major · the dream of revolution

a character of ANIMAL FARM — a member of the NOUTHESIA universe of warnings. emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦Old Major:AFM:9fe884⟧

**who —** Old Major, the prize boar whose dying vision of a world without men sparks the revolution (Marx/Lenin).
**what —** The originating ideal: he teaches Animalism and the song ‘Beasts of England,’ then dies before the revolt he inspired.
**where —** In the big barn, in the last days of his life.
**why —** Because every revolution needs its prophet — and the purity of the dream is measured against what's made of it.
**how —** By a barn-speech vision of equality and the anthem that carries it, planted before he can see it betrayed.

**the seal —** I dreamed a farm without masters and sang it to them once — and died before I could see the pigs put on the master's coat.

